column1: # # Create monthly streamflow test data from HydroBase.
# # A datevalue file is created that can be used by test command files.
# # Separate CSV files also are created for each month to simplify Python script use.
# # Only rerun if there is a real reason to do it because tests will then also have to be reverified.
# # 394308105413800 - CLEAR CR. ABV. GEORGETOWN LAKE NR GEORGETOWN
# # 394359105411900 - CLEAR CR. BLW. GEORGETOWN LAKE NR GEORGETOWN
# # Scale the second time series a bit to get more offset for visual inspection
# # Write the time series as a DateValue file in case the data need to be accessed
# # in the future without reading from HydroBase
# # Create tables for the time series for the full period and each month
# # and write as CSV files to be used as input for Python tests
# # Start with the independent time series AboveGeorgetown
# HydroBase database is: HydroBase on lonetree\CDSS
# HydroBase.db_version:  design version: 20080701  last data change: 20100801
# HydroBase table structure for software is at least 2007052520070525
# Column headings are first line below
